      "summary": ": Monday 13/7 Mōrena koutou We have a little blustery Monday for the start to your week - The groomers have been back out in action across the mountain laying down some cord and the wind is blowing around some freshies! The weather forecast for today is moderate - high winds with snow showers coming in around lunchtime. Our lifts may be subject to some wind holds today. Chains MUST be carried today as you may need them for the way home. McDougall's, Learners, White star and Valley View scheduled from 08:30 am. Captains, Soho, Willows and T-Bar to follow from 09:00am Soho and Willows recommended for advanced skiers only due to early season conditions and limited grooming.",
